delete all rows from a table (very fast)

Example table (before)
student_id	name	age	city
1	Ravi	20	Chennai
2	Kumar	21	Madurai
3	Anu	19	Coimbatore

Code
TRUNCATE TABLE students;

Result

Query OK, 0 rows affected

Check after TRUNCATE

SELECT * FROM students;

Result
Empty set (0 rows)

Table exists, but data is gone

Important points

Deletes all rows 🚫 (no WHERE allowed)

Faster than DELETE
Cannot rollback (in most cases) ❌
Resets auto-increment (very important)
